Rating: 4
This recipe is absolutely over the top fantastic. I have been making it for years to rave reviews. A tip for those who find it uneasy to spread - I add 4-5 tablespoons heavy cream to the mixture. I serve this in an oversized martini glass and scoop the mixture into the glass with an ice cream scoop. I then add a fringe of flat leaf parsley along the back of the glass by sticking the stems in the mixture. It makes a lovely presentation and is best served with Paris toasts.

