Rating: 3
This is a great appetizer and very simple. I made a lot of substitutions with what I had in the house. I used some parsley instead of chives, and used two four ounce (120 gram) logs of goat cheese: one was plain, the other herbed. I also only used 1/2 stick of butter. The result, although I'm sure different than the original recipe, is wonderful.

